# Consensus Governance Protocol (CGP)

A framework for constituent-led digital democracy.

CGP is a protocol for grassroots democratic governance that generates continuous, policy-level mandate through a triadic token system anchored to real-world fiat liabilities. Citizens deliberate on public policy in a distributed discussion substrate; politicians who deliver on ratified mandates are rewarded through an appreciating token whose value is bounded by the surplus generated by the tax pool that underwrites the system.

